<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,294,319]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Colouration and Morphology:</emphasis>
Stramineous. Crown and face without submarginal fuscous lines (Plate IIA). Crown subangularly produced; broadly triangular with dorsal marginal ridge. Genae strongly sinuate below eyes. Ocelli on margin next to eyes. Pronotum as wide as head, laterally carinate (Plate IIA).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,402,427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe subacute apically, heavily setose in posterior half; much straighter at dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,250,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Valve broadly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[559,650,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Connective “Y”-shaped with short stem (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1224,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates elongate, broader at base, tapering apically with 8–9 submarginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[983,1076,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Style with pointed apophysis; preapical lobe moderately developed (
<figureCitation box="[593,685,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with finger-like dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1307,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft nearly straight; with serrations above median length and before apex, with pair of lacerated, subequal apical processes (
<figureCitation box="[273,361,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); slightly constricted laterally above median length (
<figureCitation box="[949,1035,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,1004,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,988,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE4. Hecalus snipussp. nov. A.PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, dorsal view; C.connective, dorsal view; D.valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; E. aedeagus, dorsal view; F. aedeagus lateral view; G. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242046/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Gonopore subapical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
